  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money (from criminal activities) appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legitimate and accessible\n\nSpecific laws vary by jurisdiction, but most countries criminalize these activities through financial regulations and anti-money laundering statutes.",
